The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered a speech at Fort Hood in Texas, expressing gratitude to the men and women of the Armed Forces for their service. He also thanked the families and civilian personnel who support the military. Pence highlighted the historical significance of Fort Hood and its role in achieving victory in past wars. He praised the bravery and professionalism of the troops and emphasized their importance in the fight against terrorism. Pence also honored the fallen soldiers of Fort Hood and pledged the nation's support to their families. He reiterated President Trump's commitment to strengthening the military and praised the administration's investment in national defense. Pence concluded his speech by assuring the troops that they carry the support and prayers of the American people.